Package: corVis
Title: Visualising correlation matrices efficiently
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Amit", "Chinwan", , "amit.chinwan.2019@mumail.ie", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    person("Catherine", "Hurley", , "catherine.hurley@mu.ie", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Correlations are really useful for screening variables prior to modelling. But visualizing correrlations for a high dimensional dataset has always been a challenge. Here we propose new visualisation techniques for correlations which are efficient and each has its own advantages.
